/mnt/c3platpersistent/bin/roadside

./roadside snmp fw-default

--
This enables forwarding of V2X messages with the default configuration.
The script sets the destination IP to 127.0.0.1 and uses the default forwarding port ($FWDPORT_PSID20), which is 12345.
--

./road snmp fw-recv
--
This command uses nc (netcat) to listen on the port (12345) and prints captured data in a hex dump format.
--

Set the forwarding destination IPv4 address to localhost (127.0.0.1):
-
snmpset -v2c -c public 127.0.0.1 RSU-MIB::rsuDsrcFwdDestIpAddr.1 x 7f000001
-
Set the forwarding destination port (e.g., 12345):
-
snmpset -v2c -c public 127.0.0.1 RSU-MIB::rsuDsrcFwdDestPort.1 i 12345
-
Enable forwarding:
-
snmpset -v2c -c public 127.0.0.1 RSU-MIB::rsuDsrcFwdEnable.1 i 1
-
Optionally, set the PSID or specific message type (if required):
-
snmpset -v2c -c public 127.0.0.1 RSU-MIB::rsuDsrcFwdPsid.1 x 20
-

---
Using nc: Listen for UDP messages on the configured port:
-
nc -u -l -p 12345
-
Using tcpdump: Monitor the loopback interface for UDP packets on the forwarding port:
-
tcpdump -i lo udp port 12345 -X
